[
  {
    "startTime": 0.0,
    "endTime": 6.879,
    "text": "[Music]"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 6.879,
    "endTime": 8.24,
    "text": "you're lifting weights"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 8.24,
    "endTime": 11.12,
    "text": "the first time feels easy but each lift"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 11.12,
    "endTime": 12.88,
    "text": "takes more and more effort"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 12.88,
    "endTime": 15.599,
    "text": "until you can't continue inside your"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 15.599,
    "endTime": 16.16,
    "text": "arms"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 16.16,
    "endTime": 18.32,
    "text": "the muscles responsible for the lifting"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 18.32,
    "endTime": 21.119,
    "text": "have become unable to contract"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 21.119,
    "endTime": 24.0,
    "text": "why do our muscles get fatigued we often"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.0,
    "endTime": 24.4,
    "text": "blame"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.4,
    "endTime": 27.119,
    "text": "lactic acid or running out of energy but"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 27.119,
    "endTime": 28.32,
    "text": "these factors alone"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 28.32,
    "endTime": 30.48,
    "text": "don't account for muscle fatigue there's"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 30.48,
    "endTime": 32.32,
    "text": "another major contributor"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 32.32,
    "endTime": 34.559,
    "text": "the muscle's ability to respond to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 34.559,
    "endTime": 36.64,
    "text": "signals from the brain"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 36.64,
    "endTime": 38.16,
    "text": "to understand the roots of muscle"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 38.16,
    "endTime": 39.92,
    "text": "fatigue it helps to know how"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 39.92,
    "endTime": 42.079,
    "text": "a muscle contracts in response to a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.079,
    "endTime": 43.44,
    "text": "signal from a nerve"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 43.44,
    "endTime": 45.36,
    "text": "these signals travel from the brain to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 45.36,
    "endTime": 47.6,
    "text": "the muscles in a fraction of a second"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 47.6,
    "endTime": 51.44,
    "text": "via long thin cells called motor neurons"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 51.44,
    "endTime": 53.6,
    "text": "the motor neuron and the muscle cell are"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 53.6,
    "endTime": 54.96,
    "text": "separated by a tiny"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 54.96,
    "endTime": 57.52,
    "text": "gap and the exchange of particles across"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.52,
    "endTime": 58.32,
    "text": "this gap"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 58.32,
    "endTime": 61.12,
    "text": "enables the contraction on one side of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 61.12,
    "endTime": 61.68,
    "text": "the gap"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 61.68,
    "endTime": 63.199,
    "text": "the motor neuron contains a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 63.199,
    "endTime": 66.24,
    "text": "neurotransmitter called acetylcholine"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 66.24,
    "endTime": 68.799,
    "text": "on the other side charged particles or"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.799,
    "endTime": 69.76,
    "text": "ions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 69.76,
    "endTime": 71.76,
    "text": "line the muscle cell's membrane"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 71.76,
    "endTime": 73.6,
    "text": "potassium on the inside"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 73.6,
    "endTime": 76.88,
    "text": "and sodium on the outside in response to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 76.88,
    "endTime": 78.08,
    "text": "a signal from the brain"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 78.08,
    "endTime": 80.72,
    "text": "the motor neuron releases acetylcholine"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 80.72,
    "endTime": 82.96,
    "text": "which triggers pores on the muscle cell"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 82.96,
    "endTime": 84.72,
    "text": "membrane to open"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 84.72,
    "endTime": 88.159,
    "text": "sodium flows in and potassium flows out"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 88.159,
    "endTime": 90.72,
    "text": "the flux of these charged particles is a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 90.72,
    "endTime": 93.28,
    "text": "crucial step for muscle contraction"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 93.28,
    "endTime": 95.119,
    "text": "the change in charge creates an"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 95.119,
    "endTime": 96.4,
    "text": "electrical signal"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 96.4,
    "endTime": 98.96,
    "text": "called an action potential that spreads"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 98.96,
    "endTime": 100.24,
    "text": "through the muscle cell"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 100.24,
    "endTime": 102.399,
    "text": "stimulating the release of calcium"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 102.399,
    "endTime": 104.24,
    "text": "that's stored inside it"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 104.24,
    "endTime": 106.56,
    "text": "this flood of calcium causes the muscle"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 106.56,
    "endTime": 107.36,
    "text": "to contract"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 107.36,
    "endTime": 109.439,
    "text": "by enabling proteins buried in the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 109.439,
    "endTime": 110.479,
    "text": "muscle fibers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 110.479,
    "endTime": 112.799,
    "text": "to lock together and ratchet towards"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 112.799,
    "endTime": 115.2,
    "text": "each other pulling the muscle tight"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 115.2,
    "endTime": 117.84,
    "text": "the energy used to power the contraction"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 117.84,
    "endTime": 119.52,
    "text": "comes from a molecule called"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 119.52,
    "endTime": 123.68,
    "text": "atp atp also helps pump the ions back"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 123.68,
    "endTime": 126.24,
    "text": "across the membrane afterward resetting"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 126.24,
    "endTime": 128.56,
    "text": "the balance of sodium and potassium"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 128.56,
    "endTime": 131.28,
    "text": "on either side this whole process"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 131.28,
    "endTime": 131.84,
    "text": "repeats"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 131.84,
    "endTime": 134.4,
    "text": "every time a muscle contracts with each"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 134.4,
    "endTime": 135.2,
    "text": "contraction"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 135.2,
    "endTime": 138.4,
    "text": "energy in the form of atp gets used up"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 138.4,
    "endTime": 140.4,
    "text": "waste products like lactic acid are"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 140.4,
    "endTime": 143.2,
    "text": "generated and some ions drift away from"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 143.2,
    "endTime": 144.72,
    "text": "the muscle's cell membrane"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 144.72,
    "endTime": 147.04,
    "text": "leaving a smaller and smaller group"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 147.04,
    "endTime": 147.84,
    "text": "behind"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 147.84,
    "endTime": 150.4,
    "text": "though muscle cells use up atp as they"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 150.4,
    "endTime": 151.84,
    "text": "contract repeatedly"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 151.84,
    "endTime": 154.4,
    "text": "they are always making more so most of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 154.4,
    "endTime": 154.959,
    "text": "the time"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 154.959,
    "endTime": 157.68,
    "text": "even heavily fatigued muscles still have"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 157.68,
    "endTime": 159.92,
    "text": "not depleted this energy source"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 159.92,
    "endTime": 161.599,
    "text": "and though many waste products are"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 161.599,
    "endTime": 163.519,
    "text": "acidic fatigued muscles"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 163.519,
    "endTime": 166.48,
    "text": "still maintain ph within normal limits"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 166.48,
    "endTime": 167.76,
    "text": "indicating that the tissue"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 167.76,
    "endTime": 170.4,
    "text": "is effectively clearing these wastes but"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 170.4,
    "endTime": 171.2,
    "text": "eventually"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 171.2,
    "endTime": 173.44,
    "text": "over the course of repeated contractions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 173.44,
    "endTime": 174.959,
    "text": "there may not be sufficient"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 174.959,
    "endTime": 176.959,
    "text": "concentrations of potassium"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 176.959,
    "endTime": 179.68,
    "text": "sodium or calcium ions immediately"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 179.68,
    "endTime": 181.76,
    "text": "available near the muscle cell membrane"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 181.76,
    "endTime": 184.72,
    "text": "to reset the system properly so even if"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 184.72,
    "endTime": 186.159,
    "text": "the brain sends a signal"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 186.159,
    "endTime": 188.0,
    "text": "the muscle cell can't generate the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.0,
    "endTime": 191.12,
    "text": "action potential necessary to contract"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 191.12,
    "endTime": 193.68,
    "text": "even when ions like sodium potassium or"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 193.68,
    "endTime": 195.04,
    "text": "calcium are depleted"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 195.04,
    "endTime": 197.68,
    "text": "in or around the muscle cell these ions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 197.68,
    "endTime": 198.64,
    "text": "are plentiful"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 198.64,
    "endTime": 200.879,
    "text": "elsewhere in the body with a little time"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 200.879,
    "endTime": 202.64,
    "text": "they will flow back to the areas where"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 202.64,
    "endTime": 203.28,
    "text": "they're needed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 203.28,
    "endTime": 205.44,
    "text": "sometimes with the help of active sodium"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 205.44,
    "endTime": 207.519,
    "text": "and potassium pumps"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 207.519,
    "endTime": 210.0,
    "text": "so if you pause and rest muscle fatigue"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 210.0,
    "endTime": 210.879,
    "text": "will subside"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 210.879,
    "endTime": 213.12,
    "text": "as these ions replenish throughout the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 213.12,
    "endTime": 214.159,
    "text": "muscle"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 214.159,
    "endTime": 216.48,
    "text": "the more regularly you exercise the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 216.48,
    "endTime": 218.4,
    "text": "longer it takes for muscle fatigue to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 218.4,
    "endTime": 218.959,
    "text": "set in"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 218.959,
    "endTime": 221.12,
    "text": "each time that's because the stronger"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 221.12,
    "endTime": 223.519,
    "text": "you are the fewer times this cycle of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 223.519,
    "endTime": 225.04,
    "text": "nerve signal from the brain to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 225.04,
    "endTime": 226.64,
    "text": "contraction in the muscle"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 226.64,
    "endTime": 228.64,
    "text": "has to be repeated to lift a certain"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 228.64,
    "endTime": 229.84,
    "text": "amount of weight"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 229.84,
    "endTime": 233.04,
    "text": "fewer cycles means slower ion depletion"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 233.04,
    "endTime": 235.439,
    "text": "so as your physical fitness improves you"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 235.439,
    "endTime": 237.12,
    "text": "can exercise for longer"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 237.12,
    "endTime": 240.239,
    "text": "at the same intensity many muscles grow"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 240.239,
    "endTime": 241.28,
    "text": "with exercise"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 241.28,
    "endTime": 243.439,
    "text": "and larger muscles also have bigger"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 243.439,
    "endTime": 245.04,
    "text": "stores of atp"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 245.04,
    "endTime": 247.519,
    "text": "and a higher capacity to clear waste"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 247.519,
    "endTime": 248.56,
    "text": "pushing fatigue"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 248.56,
    "endTime": 250.63,
    "text": "even farther into the future"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 250.63,
    "endTime": 251.84,
    "text": "[Music]"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 251.84,
    "endTime": 253.76,
    "text": "now find out how to make your muscles"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 253.76,
    "endTime": 266.32,
    "text": "bigger and stronger with this video"
  }
]